7 (12) (11) Not less than 60 days after the transfer date, an
8 authority shall establish a citizens advisory council to provide
9 public input and advise the board on the impact of redevelopment
10 and management of a qualified convention facility upon the
11 qualified city and each county within the qualified metropolitan
12 area. The advisory council shall consist of 8 members, including 1
13 resident of the qualified city appointed by the local chief
14 executive officer of the qualified city, 1 resident of the
15 qualified city appointed by the legislative body of the qualified
16 city, 1 county resident appointed as a council member by each local
17 chief executive officer for each county within the qualified
18 metropolitan area, and 1 county resident appointed as a council
19 member by the legislative body for each county within the qualified
20 metropolitan area. An elected state or local official is not
21 eligible to serve as a member of the citizens advisory council.
22 Members of the advisory council shall be appointed for terms of 4
23 years. A vacancy on the advisory council arising other than by
24 expiration of a term shall be filled for the remainder of a term in
25 the same manner as the original appointment. The business of the
26 advisory council shall must be conducted at a public meeting held
27 in compliance with the open meetings act, 1976 PA 267, MCL 15.261
28 to 15.275. Public notice of the time, date, and place of the
29 meeting shall must be given in the manner required by the open
ERE H02802'25 (H-3) ys8z46

