1 meetings act, 1976 PA 267, MCL 15.261 to 15.275. The advisory
2 council shall adopt bylaws consistent with the open meetings act,
3 1976 PA 267, MCL 15.261 to 15.275, governing its procedures and the
4 holding of meetings. After organization, the advisory council shall
5 adopt a schedule of regular meetings and adopt a regular meeting
6 date, place, and time. The advisory council shall keep a written or
7 printed record of each meeting, which record and any other document
8 or record prepared, owned, used, in the possession of, or retained
9 by the advisory council in the performance of an official function
10 shall must be made available to the public in compliance with the
11 freedom of information act, 1976 PA 442, MCL 15.231 to 15.246. An
12 advisory council shall organize and make its own policies and
13 procedures and shall adopt bylaws not inconsistent with this act
14 governing its operations. The advisory council may request and
15 shall must receive from the authority information and technical
16 assistance relating to the development and management of the
17 qualified convention facility. Failure of the advisory council to
18 organize, meet, or perform statutory functions shall does not
19 prevent the board or the authority from performing authorized
20 activities. A member of the citizens advisory council shall must
21 not be compensated for being a member, nor shall and a member must
22 not be reimbursed for any expenses incurred as a member of the
23 citizens advisory council.
